entries.meaning: Something whose duration has been extended or that has been transferred to another time.
An amount, especially a sum of money, transferred to a new column in a ledger, or applied to a later time.
examples: First, as a general rule, carryover stocks are, held in countries that have lower carrying costs, which are probably exporting countries because they enjoy lower prices.

entries.meaning: The damaging condition where water droplets are carried out of a steam boiler along with the dry steam.
